CRC Card
Class: TransponderReciever
Responsibilities:
- Listen for incoming aircraft transponder broadcasts
- Receive raw high-density flight packets
- Forward received packets for decoding
Collaborators (if any):
- PacketDecoder
Assumptions (if any):
- Each aircraft broadcasts continuously while airborne 

CRC Card
Class: PacketDecoder
Responsibilities:
- Unpack raw transponder packets into structured flight data
- Parse aircraft type, identification code, altitude, speed, heading, and position
- Validate decoded data for completeness and format integrity
- Forward decoded FlightData records to AircarftDatabase
Collaborators (if any):
- TransponderReciever
- FlightData
- AircraftDatabse
Assumptions (if any):
- The packet format for aircraft data is predefined and consistent.

CRC Card
Class: Flight Data
Responsibilities:
- Store a single aircraft's flight attributes (ID, type,altitude,speed,heading,position)
- Provide access to aircraft flight information
- Represent one aircraft's current flight state
Collaborators (if any):
- PacketDecoder
- AircraftDatabase
- SafetyAnalyzer
Assumptions (if any):
- Each aircraft broadcast contains a unique identifier.

CRC Card
Class: AircraftDatabase
Responsibilities:
- Store and maintain the current FlightData record for every aircraft
- Update aircraft information when new flight data arrives
- Retrieve aircraft information for display and queries
Collaborators (if any):
- FlightData
- PacketDecoder
- RadarScreen
- DisplayCOntroller
- SafteyAnalyzer
- QueryHandler
Assumptions (if any):
- The database stores the most recent state of each aircraft.

CRC Card
Class: DisplayController
Responsibilities:
- Trigger a full radar display refresh every 10 seconds
- Retrieve all current FlightData records from AircraftDatabase
- Send the updated scene to RadarScreen for rendering
Collaborators (if any):
- AircraftDatabase
- RadarScreen
Assumptions (if any):
- Display refresh intervals are fixed at 10 seconds.

CRC Card
Class: RadarScreen
Responsibilities:
- Render aircraft positions as labled blips
- Display alerts and warnings on the graphical interface
- Update the radar display based on the latest aircraft data
Collaborators (if any):
- DisplayController
- AircraftDatabase
- DangerAlert
Assumptions (if any):
- Each aircraft is represented by a single graphical symbol on the radar screen.

CRC Card
Class: SafetyAnalyzer
Responsibilities:
- Analyze all current FlightData records to detect dangerous situations
- Evaluate aircrfat separation distances and trajectories
- Generate alerts when safety thresholds are violated
Collaborators (if any):
- AircraftDatabase
- FlightData
- DangerAlert
Assumptions (if any):
- Safety rules define minimum safe distances between aircraft.

CRC Card
Class: DangerAlert
Responsibilities:
- Represent a detected hazardous situation
- Store details of a detected dangerous situation (type, severity, involved aircraft IDs)
- Track whether the alert has been acknowledged by the controller
Collaborators (if any):
- SafetyAnalyzer
- AlertNotifier
- RadarScreen
Assumptions (if any):
- Alerts include the involved aircraft IDs and the type of hazard detected.

CRC Card
Class: AlertNotifier
Responsibilities:
- Receive active DangerAlerts from SafetyAnalyzer and display alert summary messages on ControllerConsole
- Trigger an audible or visual alarms
- Manage acknowledgment of alerts by the controller
Collaborators (if any):
- DangerAlert
- ControllerConsole
Assumptions (if any):
- Alerts remain active until acknowledged by the controller.

CRC Card
Class: QueryHandler
Responsibilities:
- Accept detail query requests from ControllerConsole for a specified aircraft
- Retrieve aircraft details from the aircraft database
- Return formatted aircraft information for display
Collaborators (if any):
- AircraftDatabase
- ControllerConsole
- FlightData
Assumptions (if any):
- Queries are based on selecting an aircraft shown on the radar screen.

CRC Card
Class: ControllerConsole
Responsibilities:
- Provide the controller interface for monitoring aircraft
- Display alerts and aircraft information
- Accept controller input such as queries or acknowledgments
Collaborators (if any):
- QueryHandler
- AlertNotifier
- RadarScreen
Assumptions (if any):
- The console acts as the primary interface used by the air traffic controller.

